title: Diamond in the Dust
description: Ian Stuart Donaldson was the first major "neo-Nazi rock star" who almost single-handed created the racist "skinhead" movement which spread all over the world from its humble beginnings in London. This account, written by one of his friends from inside the movement, provides many fascinating details of the career of one of rock music's most influential, feared, radical and shocking stars who became an icon for thousands of disaffected young white kids
